A quick litmus test for Quarto markdown syntax.  See the main
documentation for more detailed examples:
[Quarto Guide](https://quarto.org/docs/guide/){target="_blank"}.


## Basics

Quarto uses Pandoc markdown and the file extension: `*.qmd`.

### Unordered list

* Computation
  - R
  - Python
  - Observable JS
* Rendering
  - Scientific markdown (LaTeX equations, citations)
  - Graphviz diagrams
  - Mermaid diagrams
  - Code blocks with syntax formatting and annotation

### Ordered lists

You can make a typical numbered list.

1. Item one
2. Iterm two
3. Item three
    1. Item x
    2. Item y

a. Apple
b. Banana
c. Cherry
    i. Bing Cherry
    ii. Other Cherries

Auto-numbered lists that can be interrupted and resumed.

(@) Item one
    (@) Item one:one
    (@) Item one:two

something else to include

(@) Item two

A definition list

term one
: definition of term one

term two
: defintion of term two

You can also write out checklists...

- [ ] Tasks
    - [x] Tasks
    - [ ] Tasks
- [ ] Tasks

